{"name": "Arm Guard", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_05.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+1 AC, 1 lb, 10 gp</em></p><p>A fully enclosed arm shield that often had a sword built into its construction to make a gauntlet sword called a pata. Without an attached weapon, the hand which has an arm guard equipped can be used to help wield a weapon or assist with Reload, but cannot be used to wield a weapon by itself; in this case it must be attached to the arm guard.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You can attach a Light weapon to an arm guard using smith's tools over 8 hours. The weapon gains the Affixed property but can't be removed without smith's tools. When removed, the weapon is destroyed. Attack rolls made with any arm guard hand suffer a -1 penalty.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>You no longer suffer an attack penalty, you cannot be disarmed, and you can don the arm guard for free.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 10, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 1, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 1, "dex": null}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": [], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": null}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Arm Guard", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 1, "donAction": "Object Interaction"}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Buckler", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_01.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+1 AC, 2 lbs, 5 gp</em></p><p>A buckler, or target, is a hand shield used by duelists and fencers for its small profile and ease of counter attacks while deflecting. The master's trained duelist techniques set them up for the perfect riposte.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>The buckler has Finesse and Deflect (d8).</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>You can add the Deflect roll from the buckler to any Deflect roll you make with your main hand, and if this roll reduces incoming damage to 0, you can make an attack against the triggering creature as part of the same reaction.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 5, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 2, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 1, "dex": null}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": [], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": null}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Buckler", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 1, "donAction": "Object Interaction"}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Diskarmor", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_15.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+2 AC, 8 lbs, 75 gp</em></p><p>An esoteric weapon of gnomish invention, a diskarmor is a round shield attached to a chain mechanism that retracts quickly after the chain reaches its length to make essentially a shield yo-yo. The user can toss it out to wield it like a large flail, then retract it to be used as a shield again.</p><p>Diskarmor is a shield which has the following properties: One-Handed, Reach, Melee d6, Clockwork, Entangle, Trip. Diskarmor deals bludgeoning damage. A diskarmor is not considered a weapon.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You can replace any of your attacks with an attack using the Diskarmor. This attack does not benefit from your ability modifier to damage unless you have the Two-Weapon Fighting Style.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>When your ally within 10ft is hit by an attack, you can use your reaction to confer your shield AC bonus from this shield to them until the end of your next turn, possibly negating an attack.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 75, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 8, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 2, "dex": null}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": [], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": null}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Diskarmor", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 2, "donAction": "Bonus Action"}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Kite Shield", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_35.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+3 AC, 10 lbs, 30 gp</em></p><p>Kite shields are as wide as the wielder's torso but extend downward with a point or oval extension to protect the legs, which can also be used offensively to knock an enemy off guard. While wielding a Kite, you only add a maximum of +2 to your AC from your Dexterity modifier.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You gain advantage on any saving throw or ability check made to resist being knocked prone or moved along the ground.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>When you win an Athletics contest against an enemy within 5ft, you can Stagger your enemy in addition to winning the contest.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 30, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 10, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 3, "dex": 2}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": ["stealthDisadvantage"], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": 13}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Kite", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 3, "donAction": "Action", "dexLimit": 2}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Pavise", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_40.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+1 AC, 15 lbs, 35 gp</em></p><p>A pavise is a lighter tower shield with a central spike to drive into the ground, or a set of legs to allow the shield to stand freely. While deployed, you can use it as cover. Unfortunately it is unwieldable as a normal shield, only able to be worn on the back. While wearing it, you are unable to equip any other shield, and only add a maximum of +2 from your Dexterity modifier to your AC, as its size is ungainly and cumbersome.</p><p>While deployed, a Pavise can be knocked down if the enemy succeeds on an Athletics Check against your weapon DC. As a bonus action you can pick up a pavise and either deploy it again or don it on your back.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>While worn, you gain +1 AC and negate any flanking bonus any enemy might have on you. As a bonus action, you can deploy the shield to solid ground, which takes up a 5 ft square space. While the shield is between you and any enemy, you gain the benefits of half cover.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>While the shield is between you and any enemy, you gain the benefits of three-quarters cover. Additionally, an enemy has disadvantage on any roll made to knock your shield down while you use it as cover.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 35, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 15, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 1, "dex": 2}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": ["stealthDisadvantage"], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": 13}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Pavise", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 1, "donAction": "N/A", "dexLimit": 2}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Skirmish Shield", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_20.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+2 AC, 6 lbs, 10 gp</em></p><p>Skirmish shields come in a variety of shapes but are about the size of the user's torso. A Skirmish shield is large enough to provide better passive protection than the buckler, while still providing the agility missing with a tower shield. The master can extend this agility to even spell attacks and can offensively use the edge of their shield.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You gain an additional +2AC bonus against ranged weapon attacks, adding +4AC in total.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>You gain an additional +2AC bonus against ranged spell attacks, adding +4 in total, and a successful shove deals d4 + Strength modifier in bludgeoning damage.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 10, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 6, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 2, "dex": null}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": [], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": null}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Skirmish", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 2, "donAction": "Bonus Action"}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Spiked Shield", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_25.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+2 AC, 8 lbs, 20 gp</em></p><p>A spiked shield is a blanket term for all weaponized shields, with spikes on the face and either a spiked or bladed edge. Somewhat cumbersome compared to a skirmish shield with the added weaponization, a spiked shield is hard to be stealthy and agile with.</p><p>Spiked shield has the following properties: One-Handed, Melee d6, Brace, Puncture, Thrown (20/60). Spiked shield deals piercing or slashing damage. A spiked shield is not considered a weapon.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You can replace any of your attacks with an attack using the Spiked shield. This attack does not benefit from your ability modifier to damage unless you have the Two-Weapon Fighting Style.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>You are so effective at using the dangerous points or blades of your shield that all enemies suffer disadvantage to Athletics checks against you, and a successful shove deals d4 + Strength modifier in piercing or slashing damage.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 20, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 8, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 2, "dex": null}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": ["stealthDisadvantage"], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": null}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Spiked", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 2, "donAction": "Bonus Action"}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
{"name": "Tower Shield", "type": "equipment", "img": "modules/rnk-commanders-rme/assets/shields/shield_45.png", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>+3 AC, 20 lbs, 50 gp</em></p><p>This massive shield is as tall as you and just as wide; you more fight around it like a door as a piece of mobile cover. The master shieldman can take cover at a moment's notice, effectively giving the enemy no target. While wielding a tower shield, you cannot add your Dexterity modifier to your AC.</p><h3>Training Levels</h3><table class='rme-stat-table'><tr><th>Level</th><th>Properties</th></tr><tr><td><strong>Basic</strong></td><td>You negate any flanking bonus an enemy might have on you. Additionally, when you are hit with an attack or are forced to roll a Dexterity saving throw, you can use your reaction to gain half cover, possibly negating the attack or granting you a bonus to your Dexterity saving throw before you roll. This half cover lasts only for the effect that triggered your reaction.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Master</strong></td><td>While using the shield as cover, if you are subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw, and you fail that save, you take only half damage.</td></tr></table>"}, "price": {"value": 50, "denomination": "gp"}, "weight": {"value": 20, "units": "lb"}, "armor": {"value": 3, "dex": 0}, "type": {"value": "shield", "baseItem": "shield"}, "properties": ["stealthDisadvantage"], "equipped": false, "rarity": "common", "strength": 13}, "effects": [], "flags": {"rnk-commanders-rme": {"rmeData": {"group": "Shields", "shieldType": "Tower", "trainingLevel": "basic", "acBonus": 3, "donAction": "Action", "dexLimit": 0}}}, "_stats": {"systemId": "dnd5e", "systemVersion": "5.2.5"}}
